></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 25, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104awp1665702882493.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/awp1665702882493.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/awp1665702882493.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"awp1665702882493\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\"> nl \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">No linger. Allows TCP sockets to be closed without delay and not enter <code class=\"ph codeph\">TIMED_WAIT</code> state.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"awp1665702882493__topic_d32276e1_d32277e1_d32278e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"awp1665702882493__p_d32279e1_d32280e1_d32281e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$TCP_PARAMS</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">nl</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"awp1665702882493__section_jkj_tfh_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d128517e69\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"awp1665702882493__p_d32285e1_d32286e1_d32287e1\">This setting is best used in the assignment file of\n            the Uniface Router.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"awp1665702882493__section_syz_tfh_hwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d128517e78\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"awp1665702882493__p_d32291e1_d32292e1_d32293e1\">If there is a high volume of messaging, many TCP\n            sockets may end up in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">TIMED_WAIT</code> state. This can occur when using\n            web applications to call into Uniface or when sending asynchronous messages. Eventually\n            the system may run out of sockets and all new TCP communication will stop until more\n            sockets become available. In this case, it is useful to set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">nl</span>\n            option.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mal1665702690837.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Asynchronous Messaging</a><p>To communicate with each other asynchronously, Uniface components can send asynchronous messages (often known as postmessages). Components can send messages to other components running in the same Uniface client process, in other client processes, and in shared Uniface Server processes. Messages sent between different processes are transported via the Uniface Router.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525904\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525904\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "nl Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 25, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 nl No linger. Allows TCP sockets to be closed without delay and not enter TIMED_WAIT state. USYS$TCP_PARAMS { = } nl Use This setting is best used in the assignment file of the Uniface Router. Description If there is a high volume of messaging, many TCP sockets may end up in the TIMED_WAIT state. This can occur when using web applications to call into Uniface or when sending asynchronous messages. Eventually the system may run out of sockets and all new TCP communication will stop until more sockets become available. In this case, it is useful to set the nl option. Related Links Asynchronous Messaging To communicate with each other asynchronously, Uniface components can send asynchronous messages (often known as postmessages). Components can send messages to other components running in the same Uniface client process, in other client processes, and in shared Uniface Server processes. Messages sent between different processes are transported via the Uniface Router. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}